2000-09-04 11:28:56  bugg  <bugg@users.sourceforce.net>

	* /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/game_clients/lapocha/main.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/game_clients/spades/client_func.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/game_clients/tictactoe/main.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/datatypes.h, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/game.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/seats.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/easysock/easysock.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/game_clients/dots/main.c:
	Shuffle the header files around so we can
	build ggz (no ggzd yet) on the BSDs. ggz may now be
	built like such:

	curly% GTK_CONFIG="/usr/X11R6/bin/gtk12-config" \
	CPPFLAGS="-I/usr/local/include" LDFLAGS="-L/usr/local/lib" \
	./autogen.sh

	The CPPFLAGS and LDFLAGS are so it can find popt.h and -lpopt,
	respectively.  It would be nice if they searched here as well
	by default, so you'd only have to specify the location of
	gtk12-config.

2000-09-04 10:42:31  rgade  <rgade@users.sourceforce.net>

