2000-07-29 02:09:36  bcox  <bcox@users.sourceforce.net>

	* /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/ggzrc.c:
	- Squashed a bug in my previous fix of the ggzrc remove functions.
	  - I was attempting to remove a list item and then iterate to the
	    next list item using the now defunct iterator.
	  - The fix involves moving storing the hashkey contained by the
	    current list item, moving to the next element, and then freeing
	    the data last.

	* /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/ggzrc.c:
	- Remove key/section from rc_list in ggzrc_remove_{section,key}.
	  - This code is untested and may be broken, particularly at line
	    223 since I'm not sure what effect calling g_slist_remove and
	    subsequently calling g_slist_next on an iterator pointing to the
	    just-removed item will have. ;-)

