2000-04-26 21:59:57  jzaun  <jzaun@users.sourceforce.net>

	* /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/Makefile.am, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/connect.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/dlg_login.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/dlg_main.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/dlg_props.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/dlg_props.h, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/main.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/xtext.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/xtext.h, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/glade/dlg_props.glade, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/glade/main_win.glade:
	- Replaced GtkText with GtkXText custom widget
	        * Improved color supprt
	        * Split text   username | Message
	        * Scrollback - When you scrollback and a new message
	                comes in, you will _not_ be autoscrolled to
	                the bottom
	        * Timestamping
	        * Future ability for transparancy and background images
	        * GNOME support optional at build time based on ./configure
	                1) This will not and is not used currently in the GTK+
	                   only client, but will and should be used in the
	                   GNOME client.

	- Start on properties dialog
	        * Servers
	        * Chat
	                1) Font, Color usernames, and Color chat
	                   not implimented yet.
	                2) All other chat options are stored and
	                   retrieved in the ~/.ggzrc file under
	                   [CHAT]
	                3) All other chat options are functional
	        * User Information

	- Added informationl text at startup to the chat area
	        * Clinet version
	        * GTK+ Version
	        * Debug on/off
	        * socket debug on/off

	NOTE:
	        The XText widget is used with permition from Zed, the
	        author. This widget is GPLed and very suited for chat,
	        as it was designed for chat from the ground up. Useing
	        the custom widget does _not_ break compatiblity with our
	        GLADE files. GLADE has means for useing custon widgets.

	        The change over to the XText widget went smothly and all
	        things should work as they did before, with the exclustion
	        of color in the chat. I'll be working on this next with the
	        redesign of the chat protocol.

	        The properties dialog is in very early development, The GLADE
	        file is in CVS too, Please take a look and hack at it a bit.
	        The dialog should be easy to use and self explanatory to the
	        end user, not something like Microsoft(tm) uses :-)

	        Take a look at the new code, I'm bad with commenting, so if
	        you have questions give a hollar. I _will_ go back and comment
	        code. This was a large change and I wanted to get it in so others
	        could take a look and work on things they may want to.

