	* /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/callbacks.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/connect.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/game.c, /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/game.h:
	- Support {RSP|REQ}_GAME opcodes.  This removes the dirty hack I
	  was using to get the game_client and game_server to talk.
	- Exec game_client with '-o' if we need options to be set
	  (since players who join existing tables don't set options)
	- Pass flag to launch_game() if we are actually launching
	  (versus joining)

	* /cvsroot/GGZ/ggz/ggz/protocols.h:
	- Updated to newest protocols from ggzd

